args: Please note that this story contains spoilers\nfor both the Faith Forsaken (Part Two) and\nOne Starry Dragonyule events.
Our next mission is to secure a key to\nperdition and claim one of the Scrolls of\nPerdition. Quite the responsibility.
Indeed. Precisely as the name suggests,\nthese keys are required to gain access to\nthe Scrolls.
Which means another new Scroll may\nbe loosed upon the world if we fail...
Not an exaggeration to say the fate of\nthe Ilian Church rests on this mission.\nDo we know the key's location?
The details are still being investigated.\nThe mission will officially begin once the\nwhereabouts have been determined.
At present, we know only that the key\nresides somewhere in the frozen north.

...Lovely. Never been a fan of the cold,
myself. I'm an ideas man, not a snowman.
I'd rather leave the extreme climes to
someone else.
Yes, but as they are counting on that mind\nof yours, why not try being motivated?\nYou knowâ€”as a novelty.
Indeed, you two were judged to be the\nbest fit for this task due to its highly\nconfidential and uncertain nature.
That means they believe that out of all the\napostles, you, Nevin, are the one they trust\nmost to be able to adapt on the fly.
Thanks for the in-depth analysis, Pops.
All right, well, if they're going to pile the\nexpectations on me, I suppose I should\nactually try to meet 'em.
I do look forward to seeing that, as well\nas observing how much you're grown.
And I'm eager for you to finally stop\nseeing me as a kid.
Ooh, I like this! Warm and windproof?\nCozy and comfy? Sometimes it's worth\nit to spend the extra coin for bespoke.
And hoo boy, it was a LOT of coin.\nBut hey, let's just call it an early\nDragonyule present to myself.
We're putting up the Yuletree!\nCome lend a hand!
We've got more ornaments this year\nthan ever before!
Looks like everyone in town is in\nfull-on Dragonyule mode.
Too bad I can't join the fun. But sadly,\nthere's no such thing as a vacation\nin the apostle biz.
Huh? Daddy? Kid, do I look old enough to\nbe your... Wait, don't answer that.
Oops! I'm sorry, mister. Your coat's\nthe same color as my daddy's.
Whoa, hold off on the waterworks, kid!\nFolks are gonna think I did something.
Ugh. Fine, I'll help you find your old man.\nWhat's he look like?
(Kid's wearing foreign duds, so they're\nprobably tourists. That should make it\neasier to predict Dad's movements.)
Oh, thank goodness! I've been looking\neverywhere for you, Son!
Aaaand...case closed. Not that there was\never any doubt with me on the job.
Were you helping him look for me?\nThank you, kind sir. Truly.
Yes, and the fault is mine. I was so caught\nup in taking in the sights that I took my\neyes off you for a moment.
Perhaps you will permit me to make it up\nto you with a present? Anything you like!

Really. This land has a celebration called
Dragonyule where you give gifts to those
you love, and there is none I love in the
world more than you.
Yaaay! I love you too, Daddy! ...Oh, and I\nwant that thing we saw back in the store!
Jeez, kids are straightforward animals.\nBawling their eyes out one minute,\ndrooling over a gift the next.
Still, Dragonyule presents, eh?\nMan, that takes me back...
Huh? I can really have this?
Of course. Today is Dragonyule, after all.
Thanks, Ramiel! I'll take good care of it!
(I used to lose my little mind every time\nRamiel gave me a Dragonyule gift.)
(Hard to believe I was ever that innocent.)
All right, that's enough embarrassing\nflashbacks for one evening, Nevin.\nTime to go to work.
Need to make sure I'm prepared to head\nout on a moment's notice whenever\nSandalphon calls.
Let's see, next on the list is...
Huh? What's with that look, Pinon?\nDid something happen?
